name: Cafe Bappa

reviews.review_text: We landed in Goa in afternoon and were searching for a nice local restaurant. Ok the way to our Airbnb accommodation, we find this restaurant. We tried their pav with local bhaji, absolutely, absolutely delicious. Very very nice it was. Then we tried dal khichdi which was actually dal rice. Curd rice was good, but main attraction was the pav with local veg. You should go there for snacks kind of thing. They have got 2 sections, one is open and other one is with air conditioning

We saw the poster saying thali meals for 150/- and stopped. The ambience was nice and peaceful. There‚Äôs no parking space. We parked on the road side.

King fish thali was nice but very oily and side curries were all ok ok. But Pomfret thali was average. We even asked the guy to fry it again as it was not even fried well. The fish was tasteless even after frying. And he even charged 60 for extra rice which was free in some other restaurants. Overall I felt It‚Äôs average.

Too good and very cost effective.
It's a cute little place with a colorful ambience.. We had ordered batata vada, goan style puri/pav sabji. Chole sabji was the most tasty one.
They were not serving south indian food but goan food compensated for that,üòÄ
